declarations.comments: The 'accent-height' attribute controls the vertical position of an accent glyph on a text glyph (usually a vowel, like 'a', 'e', 'i', 'o', 'u') in a text element.
declarations.title: accentHeight

declarations.comments: The 'accumulate' attribute controls whether or not the animation will accumulate values over time. If specified, it indicates that the animation will preserve the previous value of the attribute being animated and add the current value to it.
declarations.title: accumulate

declarations.comments: The 'additive' attribute controls whether or not the animation will override or add to the base value of the animated attribute. If specified, it indicates that the animation will add its values to the base value of the attribute being animated. If not specified, the animation will replace the base value of the attribute being animated with its own values.
declarations.title: additive

declarations.comments: The 'alignment-baseline' attribute specifies how an element is aligned with respect to its parent baseline.
declarations.title: alignmentBaseline

declarations.comments: The 'alphabetic' attribute defines the vertical position of the text within the 'line-height' of the text element.
declarations.title: alphabetic

declarations.comments: The 'amplitude' attribute specifies the amplitude of the wave function used to distort the filter primitive.
declarations.title: amplitude

declarations.comments: The 'arabic-form' attribute controls the rendering of numbers within an SVG document. It is used to specify whether numbers should be rendered in the standard Arabic (Western) or Hindi (Eastern) numeric format.
declarations.title: arabicForm

declarations.comments: The 'ascent' attribute defines the distance from the top of the tallest glyph in the font to the baseline of the text.
declarations.title: ascent

declarations.comments: The 'attributeName' attribute specifies the name of the attribute being animated.
declarations.title: attributeName

declarations.comments: The 'attributeType' attribute specifies the namespace in which the attribute being animated is defined. It can be either 'CSS' or 'XML'.
declarations.title: attributeType

declarations.comments: The 'azimuth' attribute specifies the direction of the light source in a lighting filter.
declarations.title: azimuth

declarations.comments: The 'baseFrequency' attribute specifies the base frequency parameter for the noise function of the 'feTurbulence' filter primitive.
declarations.title: baseFrequency

declarations.comments: The 'baseline-shift' attribute specifies how much an element is shifted up or down from its baseline position.
declarations.title: baselineShift

declarations.comments: The 'baseProfile' attribute specifies the version of SVG that the document conforms to.
declarations.title: baseProfile

declarations.comments: The 'bbox' attribute indicates the tight bounding box of the current object. It's used for layout.
declarations.title: bbox

declarations.comments: The 'begin' attribute specifies the begin time for the element, when it becomes active in the animation timeline.
declarations.title: begin

declarations.comments: The 'bias' attribute indicates the slope bias for the light filter kernel.
declarations.title: bias

declarations.comments: The 'by' attribute specifies the offset from the initial value to the final value of the animation.
declarations.title: by

declarations.comments: The 'calcMode' attribute specifies the calculation mode for the animation function.
declarations.title: calcMode

declarations.comments: The 'cap-height' attribute specifies the height of the capital letters in the font.
declarations.title: capHeight

declarations.comments: The 'class' attribute specifies the class(es) for an element.
declarations.title: class_

declarations.comments: The 'clip' attribute specifies the clipping region for an element.
declarations.title: clip

declarations.comments: The 'clip-path' attribute specifies the clipping path for an element.
declarations.title: clipPath

declarations.comments: The 'clip-rule' attribute only applies to graphics elements that are contained within a 'clipPath' element. The 'clip-rule' attribute basically works as the 'fill-rule' attribute, except that it applies to 'clipPath' definitions.
declarations.title: clipRule

declarations.comments: The 'clipPathUnits' attribute defines the coordinate system for the contents of the 'clipPath' element.
declarations.title: clipPathUnits

declarations.comments: The 'color' attribute specifies the color of the text.
declarations.title: color

declarations.comments: The 'color-interpolation' attribute specifies the color space for gradient interpolations, color animations, and alpha compositing.
declarations.title: colorInterpolation

declarations.comments: The 'color-interpolation-filters' attribute specifies the color space for imaging operations performed via filter effects.
declarations.title: colorInterpolationFilters

declarations.comments: The 'color-profile' attribute specifies the name of the color profile to use when performing color correction operations within a filter primitive.
declarations.title: colorProfile

declarations.comments: The 'color-rendering' attribute provides a hint to the SVG user agent about how to optimize its color interpolation and compositing operations.
declarations.title: colorRendering

declarations.comments: The 'contentScriptType' attribute specifies the default scripting language for the given document fragment.
declarations.title: contentScriptType

declarations.comments: The 'contentStyleType' attribute specifies the default style sheet language for the given document fragment.
declarations.title: contentStyleType

declarations.comments: The 'cursor' attribute specifies the mouse cursor displayed when the mouse pointer is over an element.
declarations.title: cursor

declarations.comments: The 'cx' attribute defines the x-axis coordinate of the center of the circle.
declarations.title: cx

declarations.comments: The 'cy' attribute defines the y-axis coordinate of the center of the circle.
declarations.title: cy

declarations.comments: The 'd' attribute defines a path to be drawn.
declarations.title: d

declarations.comments: The 'descent' attribute specifies the suggested distance that the author recommends between the baselines of adjacent rows.
declarations.title: descent

declarations.comments: The 'diffuseConstant' attribute specifies the diffuse constant of the light source for the light filter kernel.
declarations.title: diffuseConstant

declarations.comments: The 'direction' attribute specifies the base direction of directionally neutral text and the directionality of tables.
declarations.title: direction

declarations.comments: The 'display' attribute specifies whether or not the given element is rendered.
declarations.title: display

declarations.comments: The 'divisor' attribute specifies the divisor for the light filter kernel.
declarations.title: divisor

declarations.comments: The 'dominant-baseline' attribute specifies a baseline shift that should be applied to the dominant-baseline of all of the glyphs corresponding to a particular graphics element.
declarations.title: dominantBaseline

declarations.comments: The 'dur' attribute specifies the simple duration of the animation.
declarations.title: dur

declarations.comments: The 'dx' attribute specifies a shift along the x-axis on the position of an element's text or the position of a 'tspan' element's text.
declarations.title: dx

declarations.comments: The 'dy' attribute specifies a shift along the y-axis on the position of an element's text or the position of a 'tspan' element's text.
declarations.title: dy

declarations.comments: The 'edgeMode' attribute specifies which edge condition is to be used to determine the values of pixels that lie outside the filter region.
declarations.title: edgeMode

declarations.comments: The 'elevation' attribute specifies the light source elevation angle in the light filter kernel.
declarations.title: elevation

declarations.comments: The 'enable-background' attribute specifies the color space for imaging operations performed via filter effects.
declarations.title: enableBackground

declarations.comments: The 'end' attribute specifies the end time for the element, when it becomes inactive in the animation timeline.
declarations.title: end

declarations.comments: The 'exponent' attribute specifies the exponent value for the light filter kernel.
declarations.title: exponent

declarations.comments: The 'externalResourcesRequired' attribute specifies whether or not to force various resource attributes to take into account external resource references.
declarations.title: externalResourcesRequired

declarations.comments: The 'fill' attribute specifies the color used to paint the element.
declarations.title: fill

declarations.comments: The 'fill-opacity' attribute specifies the opacity of the painting operation used to paint the interior the current object.
declarations.title: fillOpacity

declarations.comments: The 'fill-rule' attribute specifies the algorithm which is to be used to determine what parts of the canvas are included inside the shape.
declarations.title: fillRule

declarations.comments: The 'filter' attribute specifies the filter effects defined by the 'filter' element.
declarations.title: filter

declarations.comments: The 'filterRes' attribute specifies the width and height on the intermediate images in a filter chain.
declarations.title: filterRes

declarations.comments: The 'filterUnits' attribute specifies the coordinate system for attributes 'x', 'y', 'width' and 'height'.
declarations.title: filterUnits

declarations.comments: The 'flood-color' attribute specifies the color to use when applying the 'flood' filter primitive.
declarations.title: floodColor

declarations.comments: The 'flood-opacity' attribute specifies the opacity value to use across the current filter primitive subregion.
declarations.title: floodOpacity
